The edit was successful with no linter errors."},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You will now only capture and save the WallpaperCanvas area as the wallpaper—without the sliders or top bar overlays.

**How this works:**
- The app measures the WallpaperCanvas bounds onscreen (using `onGloballyPositioned` and `boundsInWindow`).
- When saving, it waits two frames (to ensure overlays are hidden), then PixelCopy's just that section of the window.
- The resulting bitmap excludes toolbars/sliders/text and is exactly the “editable region” you see.

You can run and test—it should save only your effect region, not the editor UI, as the wallpaper. If you want to fine-tune the crop or add a border, let me know!"}]}]}

